article.headline: Adam Clark scores 19 as Merrimack earns 65-51 victory over Vermont
article.description: — Adam Clark had 19 points in Merrimack's 65-51 win over Vermont in the Warriors season opener on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Adam Clark scores 19 as Merrimack earns 65-51 victory over Vermont
article.story: NORTH ANDOVER, Mass. -- — Adam Clark had 19 points in Merrimack's 65-51 win over Vermont in the Warriors season opener on Saturday night. Clark added six rebounds, six assists, and three steals for the Warriors. Sean Trumper added 11 points while finishing 5 of 11 from the floor while they also had seven rebounds. Matt Becht had 11 points and finished 3 of 7 from 3-point range. TJ Long finished with 22 points and two steals for the Catamounts (1-2). TJ Hurley added 11 points and two steals for Vermont. Noah Barnett finished with five points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
